</a>
<br>
<center> Loving pet, err husband, of Madchen Firestorm (The Happy SK)</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 9:22:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is offhand linked to main hand?</span><hr size=1> Offhand is not linked to main hand, it is independant.  When your offhand weapon delay comes up you make a DW skill check, if it suceeds you attack with offhander.  If you attack you make a DA check and if successfully attack twice. <p>Gorlab 56 Warrior<BR>
Tenakha 52 Druid<BR>
Keepers of the Faith</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utalicmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talic Moore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 9:22:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.darkageofcamelot.com/concept/elfw.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is offhand linked to main hand?</span><hr size=1> I was always under the impression that whenever your weapon's delay determined it should be slashing (in other words if you had a 20 delay weapon it would roll every 2.0 seconds) the game rolled and (depending on your skill) would determine if you had the opportunity to swing with that hand. I could be horribly wrong, but that seems to be the most logical way for it to work. <p>Talic Asaria Moore--
Kalrathi Blademasters--
Bristlebane Server--
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucattieluv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cattie Luv</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/15/01 10:32:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://fp.geocities.com/dafreako/eqpics/catside.gif HEIGHT=255 WIDTH=132></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is offhand linked to main hand?</span><hr size=1> Correct, whenever the offhand is ready to swing, you roll a Dual Wield skill check. if thats successful you roll a doubleattack(twice if your 60). then roll chance to hit on the 0-3 attacks you might have gotten.<br>
 <p>/Cattie Luv <br>
<a href=www.dakor.net>Da`Kor</a><br>
