<br>
if your prim hand is a 10/20 weap, it will swing (or check to swing) every 2 seconds.<br>
<br>
if your sec hand is a 10/21 weap, it will check to swing every 2.1 seconds, and it will swing when the primary's next swing is, basically, every other swing of your prim hand, your sec weap will get a chance at a swing. so that 21dly just changed to a 40.<br>
<br>
this is the way I was told, and the way I understood it please correct me if I am wrong. so if you can't get a wep for your sec that is of the same ratio, or lower than your prim, get as close to the double as you can. so if you have a langseaux in your prim, go with something that is 46dly, or under (if you can't fill your sec with something 23 or lower). so if you are using a langseaux, go with something like a unicorn shield (unless you can afford better, just an example). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/01 6:02:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my understanding</span><hr size=1> That is incorrect paragon, scroll up to the previous posts here to read how it works. <p>Gorlab 56 Warrior<BR>
Tenakha 52 Druid<BR>
Keepers of the Faith</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ueggarallanpoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EggarAllanpoe</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.pacbell.net/mcherry5/screenshots/eggar.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/01 8:34:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my understanding</span><hr size=1> Its pretty easy to verify that the hands are not linked.  Put a high delay weapon (wurmslayer) in your primary and a low delay - that is NOT slashing - (FS Dagger) in your off hand.  If the hands were linked, you would only get a pierce possible AFTER each slash.  Try it.  You'll find you get way more pierces than slashes.<br>
<br>
